description: Try our easy to follow Star Lord Lunch recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
keywords: Mains,Pescatarian,Low salt,Tree nut free,Egg free,Low sugar,Sesame free,Grape,Fish,Microwave,High protein,High fibre,Rice,Sweet potato,Low fat
name: Star Lord Lunch Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 95g can tuna in springwater, drained and flaked

recipeInstructions.text: Lunch: To make tuna & cucumber wrap, combine tuna with yoghurt. Spread mixture over wraps. Top with cucumber and roll. Cut into rounds. Pack into lunch box with grapes.

Snack 1: To make sweet potato, brown rice & feta space balls, Preheat oven to 180oC. Line a baking tray with baking paper. Place sweet potato and 1 tbs water in a microwave-safe dish. Cover and microwave on high for 3-4 minutes or until tender. Cool. Place sweet potato in a bowl and mash until smooth. Add rice, sunflower seeds and feta and stir to combine. Roll tablespoons of mixture into 12 balls and place on prepared tray. Spray lightly with oil and bake, turning halfway through cooking time, for 15 minutes or until golden. Cool completely. Place in an airtight container in fridge until ready to pack in lunch box. Serves 4 (makes 12) 3. Snack 2: To make fruit & seed yoghurt, top yoghurt with pepitas and sultanas. note: sweet potato, brown rice & feta space balls recipe serves 4
